      "heading_context_raw": "PART 12 RH - unassigned extracted text",
      "text": "Max. 4 Storey Garden : 35 m 2 / Building Max. Footprint: 500 m 2 Parking Side or Rear Max. 4 buildings / cluster / lot Streetwall Stepback on 4th Storey Min. 6 m Separation Figure 12.1 Cluster Housing Configuration - Multi-unit Dwellings .3 Cluster housing permits more than one building per lot so long as the following requirements are met: (a) Coverage max. 60% (b) Footprint / building max. 800 m 2 (c) Buildings max. 4 buildings per cluster per lot (d) Separation between units min. 6 m (e) Central garden area min. 35 m 2 / building Max. 4 Storey Garden : 35 m 2 / Building Max. Footprint: 500 m 2 Parking Side or Rear requirements are met in Section 12.3.2 for both the flaglot and main lot. .2 Permitted encroachments into the setbacks are listed in Table 3.2. .3 Home occupations are permitted if Section 4.8 requirements are met. .4 Neighbourhood local commercial is permitted in the RH Zone along any collector or arterial road as identified in Schedule C up to a gross floor area of 120 m 2 and by meeting the following requirements: (a) Three dedicated off-street automobile parking spaces and 2 Class B biking parking spaces; and (b) A minimum 1.5 m wide hard surface sidewalk linking the front entry of the store with the parking area. (c) A landscape buffer 2 m wide shall be constructed which includes an opaque fence no less than 1.8 m high along all properties that directly abut the commercial use or any associated parking. One overall Lot Parking is located on the side or rear, not the front Sidewalk connects each unit to the street Hard Surfaced Parking Max. 6 units Consecutive Units Figure 12.3 Townhouse Configuration Perpendicular to the Street .8 Townhouses may be oriented perpendicular to the street as long as (a) The building has frontage on a street and meets the fire code requirements. (b) Provides a connected walkway from each door to the street (c) Parking is in the rear or side yard (d) The building is located on one lot such that units are rental or condominium .9 The amenity requirements in Section 3.13 shall be followed. .10 For multi-unit buildings, each grade-related unit shall include a patio door.",
